        <linkGrp type="notes"/>
        <div n="947BROGP" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-947BROGP-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-947BROGP-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-947BROGP-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">UPON PRAISING HER HUSBAND TO DR SWIFT</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-947BROGP-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-947BROGP-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-947BROGP-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-947BROGP-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-947BROGP-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-947BROGP-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-947BROGP-line-1"> You always are making a god of your spouse,&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-947BROGP-line-2"> But this neither reason nor conscience allows;</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-947BROGP-line-3"> Perhaps you will say, 'tis in gratitude due,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-947BROGP-line-4"> And you adore him, because he adores you.</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-947BROGP-line-5"> Your argument's weak, and so you will find,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-947BROGP-line-6"> For you, by this rule, must adore all mankind.947BROGP   </l></lg></div>
      </div>
